        "text": "The document page discusses the uplift costs from guarantee payments in New York for the years 2016 and 2017. In 2017, the total uplift cost was $38 million, a 12% decrease from 2016's $43 million. The decline was mainly in Western New York, which saw a 49% reduction, and Long Island, with a 38% reduction. These reductions were due to less reliability commitment and out-of-market (OOM) dispatch. The local uplift in Western New York decreased significantly due to transmission upgrades and the expiration of the Milliken RSSA. The remaining local uplift could be eliminated if constraints were modeled in NYISO\u2019s day-ahead and real-time markets.\n\nAdditionally, the DAMAP, Min Oil Burn, and EDRP/SCR categories saw a reduction of over $5 million. Most uplift charges in 2016 occurred during high load days in July and August, which were not present in 2017 due to milder weather.",
