      "text": "NYISO Begins to Roll-Out Tariff Revisions for Order No. 2023 Compliance | Foley Hoag LLP - Energy & Climate Counsel - JDSupra\n \nJanuary 18, 2024\n# NYISO Begins to Roll-Out Tariff Revisions for Order No. 2023 Compliance\n[Devlyn Tedesco] \n[Foley Hoag LLP - Energy & Climate Counsel] \n+ FollowxFollowingxFollowing- Unfollow[Contact] \n**LinkedIn\n**Facebook\nX\n[**Send] \n**Embed\nTo embed, copy and paste the code into your website or blog:\n\\ \\ \n![Foley Hoag LLP - Energy &amp; Climate Counsel] \nThis post is a continuation of our series covering the New York Independent System Operator, Inc.&rsquo;s (&ldquo;NYISO&rdquo;) compliance with Federal Energy Regulatory Commission (&ldquo;FERC&rdquo;)[Order] No. 2023. Compliance filings are due to FERC by April 3, 2024.\nThe NYISO has spent the last few months developing its compliance plan for Order No. 2023 and now has a fully-formed proposal that will effectuate its new Cluster Study Process. The highlights of this new interconnection process include:\n*",
